<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1398,265,359]" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">
COLOUR. Body black; palpi and legs yellow or reddish yellow (except for black coxae and metatarsus); wings with brownish yellow setae; wing venation brown, pterostigma dark brown, with a small basal yellow spot (
<figureCitation box="[343,438,332,359]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,805,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-180@7.[189,1398,805,1822]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 2. Microplitis alborziensisAbdoli &amp; Talebi sp. nov., holotype, ♀, TMUC-HBMMP0001. A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Head, dorsal view.C. Mesosoma, dorsal view.D. Fore wing. E. Hind wing.F. Metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690334" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690334/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1398,396,536]" box="[189,358,396,423]" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,358,396,423]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,358,396,423]" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">DNA barcode</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1398,396,536]" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">
The DNA barcode sequences of 
<taxonomicName authority="Abdoli &amp; Talebi &amp; Fernandez-Triana &amp; Farahani, 2021" authorityName="Abdoli &amp; Talebi &amp; Fernandez-Triana &amp; Farahani" authorityYear="2021" box="[586,868,441,467]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Microplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alborziensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[586,868,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">Microplitis alborziensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[878,972,442,468]" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
specimen is available at the NCBI database (National 
<collectingRegion box="[425,503,475,501]" country="France" name="Centre" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">Center</collectingRegion>
for Biotechnology Information: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/; accession number: MN820452.1).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1399,573,769]" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">
The available data in NCBI shows that two specimens, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Forster" authorityYear="1862" box="[874,1003,573,599]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Microplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[874,1003,573,599]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">Microplitis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
jft111 (European, 
<collectingCountry box="[1235,1331,573,599]" name="Sweden" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">Sweden</collectingCountry>
, with accession numbers of NCBI: HM396982.1) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Forster" authorityYear="1862" box="[795,924,607,633]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Microplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[795,924,607,633]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">Microplitis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
jft112 (North American, Alaska, with accession numbers of NCBI: HM397413.1), for which there are DNA barcodes available (all based from specimens in the CNC) differ by 1.7% base pairs (11 base pairs of difference) and 1.6% base pairs (10 base pairs of difference), respectively, suggesting that they are different species (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith M. A. &amp; Fernandez-Triana J. L. &amp; Eveleigh E. &amp; Gomez J. &amp; Guclu C. &amp; Hallwachs W. &amp; Hebert P. D. &amp; Hrcek J. &amp; Huber J. T. &amp; Janzen D. &amp; Mason P. G. &amp; Miller S. &amp; Quicke D. L. J. &amp; Rodriguez J. J. &amp; Rougerie R. &amp; Shaw M. R. &amp; Varkonyi G. &amp; Ward D. F. &amp; Whitfield J. B. &amp; Zaldivar-Riveron A." pageId="8" pageNumber="91" pagination="168 - 176" refId="ref17471" refString="Smith M. A., Fernandez-Triana J. L., Eveleigh E., Gomez J., Guclu C., Hallwachs W., Hebert P. D., Hrcek J., Huber J. T., Janzen D., Mason P. G., Miller S., Quicke D. L. J., Rodriguez J. J., Rougerie R., Shaw M. R., Varkonyi G., Ward D. F., Whitfield J. B. &amp; Zaldivar-Riveron A. 2013. DNA barcoding and the taxonomy of Microgastrinae wasps (Hymenoptera, Braconidae): impacts after 8 years and nearly 20000 sequences. Molecular Ecology Resources 13 (2): 168 - 176. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / 1755 - 0998.12038" type="journal article" year="2013">
Smith 
<emphasis box="[1337,1399,708,734]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
for further details).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="91" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,303,806,832]" box="[189,303,806,832]" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,806,832]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,806,832]" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[188,1399,851,1046]" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">
<taxonomicName authority="Abdoli &amp; Talebi &amp; Fernandez-Triana &amp; Farahani, 2021" authorityName="Abdoli &amp; Talebi &amp; Fernandez-Triana &amp; Farahani" authorityYear="2021" box="[189,467,851,877]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Microplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alborziensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,467,851,877]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">Microplitis alborziensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[473,562,851,877]" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
runs to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wesmael, 1937)" baseAuthorityName="Wesmael" baseAuthorityYear="1937" box="[653,1034,851,877]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Microplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculifer">
<emphasis box="[653,828,851,877]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">M. tuberculifer</emphasis>
(Wesmael, 1937)
</taxonomicName>
in the key provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Telenga N. A." pageId="8" pageNumber="91" pagination="1 - 311" refId="ref17698" refString="Telenga N. A. 1955. Braconidae, subfamily Microgastrinae, subfamily Agathinae. Fauna USSR, Hymenoptera. Zoological Institute of the Academy of Science of the U. S. S. R. 5 (4): 1 - 311." type="journal article" year="1955">Telenga (1955)</bibRefCitation>
and runs to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Thomson, 1895)" baseAuthorityName="Thomson" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[427,848,884,911]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Microplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trochanterata">
<emphasis box="[427,630,884,910]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">M. trochanterata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Thomson C. G." box="[649,840,884,911]" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" pagination="2141 - 2339" refId="ref17744" refString="Thomson C. G. 1895. LII. Bidrag till Braconidernas Kannedom. Opuscula Entomologica 20: 2141 - 2339." type="journal article" year="1895">Thomson, 1895</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in the key of 
<bibRefCitation author="Tobias V. I." box="[1029,1196,884,911]" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" refId="ref17825" refString="Tobias V. I. 1986. Subfamily Microgastrinae. In: Medvedev G. S. (ed.) Keys to the Insects of the European Part of the USSR. Volume III. Part IV. Amerind Publishing Co., New Delhi." type="book" year="1986">Tobias (1986)</bibRefCitation>
(Tobias’ species was later synonymized with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Broad et al. 2016))" baseAuthorityName="Broad" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[535,967,918,945]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Microplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculifer">
<emphasis box="[535,713,918,944]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">M. tuberculifer</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Broad G. R. &amp; Shaw M. R. &amp; Godfray H. C. J." box="[731,948,918,945]" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" pagination="8151" refId="ref14989" refString="Broad G. R., Shaw M. R. &amp; Godfray H. C. J. 2016. Checklist of British and Irish Hymenoptera-Braconidae. Biodiversity Data Journal 4: e 8151. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / BDJ. 4. e 8151" type="journal article" year="2016">
Broad 
<emphasis box="[815,876,918,944]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
))
</taxonomicName>
. It can, however, be separated from 
<taxonomicName box="[189,363,952,978]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Microplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculifer">
<emphasis box="[189,363,952,978]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">M. tuberculifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following characters: (1) T1 length/width ratio is 2.0 vs 2.5–3.0 in 
<taxonomicName box="[1216,1391,952,978]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Microplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculifer">
<emphasis box="[1216,1391,952,978]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">M. tuberculifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, (2) antenna shorter than body vs slightly longer than body in 
<taxonomicName box="[899,1075,986,1012]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Microplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculifer">
<emphasis box="[899,1075,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">M. tuberculifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, (3) tegula black vs reddish yellow to brown in 
<taxonomicName box="[419,595,1019,1045]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Microplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculifer">
<emphasis box="[419,595,1019,1045]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">M. tuberculifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1400,1083,1245]" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">
The new species runs to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Haliday, 1834)" authorityName="Belokobylskij et al." authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Haliday" baseAuthorityYear="1834" box="[485,823,1083,1110]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Microplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mediator">
<emphasis box="[485,630,1083,1109]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">M. mediator</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Haliday A. H." box="[646,815,1083,1110]" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" pagination="225 - 259" refId="ref16111" refString="Haliday A. H. 1834. Essay on parasitic Hymenoptera. Entomological Magazine 2 (3): 225 - 259." type="journal article" year="1834">Haliday, 1834</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in the key of 
<bibRefCitation author="Kotenko A. G." box="[991,1179,1083,1110]" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" pagination="134 - 192" refId="ref16413" refString="Kotenko A. G. 2007. Microgastrinae. In: Lelej A. S. (ed.) Key to the Insects of Russia Far East. Vol. IV. Neuropteroidea, Mecoptera, Hymenoptera. Pt 5: 134 - 192. Dalnauka, Vladivostok. [In Russian.]" type="journal article" year="2007">Kotenko (2007)</bibRefCitation>
from which it can be separated by: (1) head in dorsal view more transverse (i.e., its width/length ratio 1.90) vs head in dorsal view less transverse (i.e., its width/length ratio 1.60–1.70) in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Belokobylskij et al." authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Haliday" baseAuthorityYear="1834" box="[996,1141,1151,1177]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Microplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mediator">
<emphasis box="[996,1141,1151,1177]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">M. mediator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, (2) hind legs yellow, metasomal tergites and scape black vs hind legs dark brown, metasomal tergites and scape reddish yellow to red in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Belokobylskij et al." authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Haliday" baseAuthorityYear="1834" box="[381,526,1218,1244]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Microplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mediator">
<emphasis box="[381,526,1218,1244]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">M. mediator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1399,1282,1410]" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">
This species runs to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Ruthe, 1860)" baseAuthorityName="Ruthe" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[447,767,1282,1309]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Microgaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aduncus">
<emphasis box="[447,588,1282,1308]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">M. aduncus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ruthe J. F." box="[608,759,1282,1309]" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" pagination="105 - 160" refId="ref17238" refString="Ruthe J. F. 1860. Deutsche Braconiden. Erstes Stuck. Berliner entomologische Zeitschrift 4: 105 - 160." type="journal article" year="1860">Ruthe, 1860</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Papp J." box="[814,966,1283,1309]" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" pagination="95 - 140" refId="ref16754" refString="Papp J. 1984. Palaearctic species of Microgaster Latreille (= Microplitis Forster) with description of seven new species (Hymenoptera, Braconidae, Microgastrinae). Entomologische Abhandlungen 47: 95 - 140." type="journal article" year="1984">Papp (1984)</bibRefCitation>
, however, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ruthe" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[1101,1243,1282,1308]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Microgaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aduncus">
<emphasis box="[1101,1243,1282,1308]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">M. aduncus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Abdoli &amp; Talebi &amp; Fernandez-Triana &amp; Farahani, 2021" authorityName="Abdoli &amp; Talebi &amp; Fernandez-Triana &amp; Farahani" authorityYear="2021" box="[189,371,1316,1342]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Microplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alborziensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,371,1316,1342]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">M. alborziensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[378,470,1317,1343]" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
as follows: in 
<taxonomicName authority="Abdoli &amp; Talebi &amp; Fernandez-Triana &amp; Farahani, 2021" authorityName="Abdoli &amp; Talebi &amp; Fernandez-Triana &amp; Farahani" authorityYear="2021" box="[645,827,1316,1342]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Microplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alborziensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[645,827,1316,1342]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">M. alborziensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[834,925,1317,1343]" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
meso- and metafemora are yellow, vein cu-a in hind wing is slightly curved, and T1 is rugose to rugulose, whereas in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ruthe" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[1129,1268,1350,1376]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Microgaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aduncus">
<emphasis box="[1129,1268,1350,1376]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">M. aduncus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
meso- and metafemora are dark brown to black, vein cu-a in hind wing is distinctly curved, and T1 is smooth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
